Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.47,0:01:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that should be settled.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.17,0:01:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what Mother will be sending us. {as presents}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.31,0:01:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote and told her we’ve plenty of friends with good appetites here, so have no fear. {lit: glutton/gourmand}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.28,0:01:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There’ll surely be a feast so big \Nit could feed us for a month. {lit: she'll send a feast so big we won't be able to eat it}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.35,0:01:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t wait... \NLet’s make it a splendid party.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.43,0:01:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. \NOh, shall we pop by the cake shop?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.09,0:02:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.17,0:02:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that looks delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.22,0:02:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I daresay Mother will bake us \Na pie or something as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.16,0:02:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’d like a cake smothered in whipped cream.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.06,0:02:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that would please everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.86,0:02:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s dear—perhaps a bit extravagant?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.63,0:02:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.10,0:02:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our birthday,\Nit only comes once a year.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.07,0:02:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,True enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.57,0:02:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, do keep up with your studies \Nand your games this week,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.19,0:02:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and spend your days in good cheer.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.56,0:02:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s one recent thing \NI must caution you about.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.46,0:02:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It concerns birthday parties.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.92,0:02:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all very well to celebrate \None another’s birthdays—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.70,0:02:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but some of these parties \Nare becoming rather too grand. {/flashy}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.98,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do take care not to spend too much money, \Nnor to make a competition of the presents. {meaning brag to each other "I got a better gift"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.23,0:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s dampened things a bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.30,0:03:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when our birthday was round the corner...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.70,0:03:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was all set to hatch a plan too...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.64,0:03:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s what the headmistress \Nwas talking about? {lit: why she said such a thing}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.91,0:03:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.01,0:03:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, those third form girls had food brought up from a town restaurant
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.87,0:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave a grand party!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.95,0:03:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They must be rolling in money!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.05,0:03:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It caused such a stir that word reached the headmistress herself.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.11,0:03:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's what it was?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.46,0:03:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, there’s no problem.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.93,0:03:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.83,0:03:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve no intention to spend a fortune on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.87,0:03:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a clever idea or two and a party with a twist—\Nthere’s nothing wrong with that! {/to make it a unique party}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.24,0:03:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.66,0:04:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we had a midnight feast \Nfor Janet’s birthday,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.94,0:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so it ought to be something \Nthat takes everyone by surprise.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.91,0:04:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, let’s not do anything fancy. \NJust sit down to tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.98,0:04:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? \NOn {\i1}our{\i0} birthday?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.15,0:04:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We could play games, or... {lit: game tournament}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.65,0:04:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! A fancy-dress party \Nwould be marvellous! {/masquerade}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.32,0:04:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Do be sensible, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.59,0:04:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you simply going to ignore \Nwhat Headmistress said?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.56,0:04:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re so timid, sis.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.10,0:04:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’ll be fine, as long as we don’t get caught.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.00,0:04:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I won’t stand for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.04,0:04:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You, I know—you never back down \Nonce you’ve got something into your head.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.24,0:04:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one dreadful fault you have.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.08,0:04:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Isabel, are always playing \NGoody Two-Shoes! {/the good girl}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.28,0:04:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re told not to do something, \Nyou just give in without a word.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.55,0:04:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you think that’s dull?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.62,0:04:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to play Goody Two-Shoes at all!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.19,0:04:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you who is reckless, \Nheedless, even!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.66,0:04:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Like with Mam’zelle’s essay that one time.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.78,0:04:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? \NIs everything bad that happens my fault now?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.83,0:04:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I never asked you to follow my lead. \NPray, do as you please!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.20,0:05:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I shall do exactly as I please.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.87,0:05:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I’ll do just as I like too.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.46,0:05:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You mean you’re giving \Ntwo separate birthday parties?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.43,0:05:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. \NMine's at two o’clock this Sunday.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.72,0:05:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine's at three.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.22,0:05:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The time’s short, but do come to both.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.41,0:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but what on earth\Nis the matter with you two?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.03,0:05:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You girls are acting oddly.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.23,0:05:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t tell me you’ve quarrelled?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.74,0:05:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How strange!\NThe twin sisters, quarrelling?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.44,0:05:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re allowed to differ sometimes, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.91,0:05:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Just because our faces are alike \Ndoesn’t mean our minds are too.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.95,0:05:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well of course. We’d hate it if you \Nwere alike in every way. That’d be horrid.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.22,0:05:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, this is no laughing matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.79,0:05:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth started it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.89,0:06:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarrelling’s not at all like Pat and Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.48,0:06:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.60,0:06:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A birthday doesn’t mean a thing \Nunless you celebrate it together.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.95,0:06:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let them be! Better to quarrel it out \Nthoroughly than not at all. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.92,0:06:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We’ve always been lumped together in everything.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But from now on, we want to be treated as two separate people.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.86,0:06:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We’re giving up being the twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.30,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. I am Isabel O’Sullivan. \NPat is Patricia O’Sullivan.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.99,0:06:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re never, ever \Nto call us “the twins” again. {futago-chan}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.21,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure, understood, the twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.69,0:06:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.16,0:07:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.24,0:07:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.76,0:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{dunno what to put here}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.23,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, stop teasing.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.70,0:07:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll only make it harder for them to make up.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.72,0:07:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t worry, Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.70,0:07:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two are always in step with one another. {lit: breathing is perfectly synced}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.00,0:07:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to change rooms?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.94,0:07:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’d like to move next door.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.39,0:07:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila has offered to swap with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.63,0:07:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But why, for Pete's sake?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.19,0:07:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.33,0:07:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Patricia.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.36,0:07:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless there’s a very special reason, \Nyou can’t change rooms in the middle of term.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.92,0:07:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.77,0:07:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Has something happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.50,0:07:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.40,0:08:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are your test papers back. \NFar too many mistakes this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.41,0:08:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do listen and make notes properly.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.78,0:08:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then—Patricia and Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.30,0:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.77,0:08:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.96,0:08:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.71,0:08:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiens! Have you changed seats?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.65,0:08:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui. Mam’zelle, I’ve also got a favour to ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.40,0:08:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.80,0:08:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You always call up \NIsabel and me together.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.92,0:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like you to stop that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.67,0:08:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My... But why?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.68,0:08:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You make it sound as if the two of us \Nonly add up to one person.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.34,0:08:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You call the others one by one, don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.45,0:08:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s true, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.15,0:08:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, would you prefer it that way too?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.60,0:08:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way is fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.59,0:08:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How odd! You two are behaving strangely today.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.49,0:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.94,0:08:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle, they quarrelled yesterday,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.76,0:08:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they’re fighting \Na war of independence from being twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.80,0:08:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mon dieu! Bringing a family quarrel \Ninto class—how abominable!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.78,0:09:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia and Isabel,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.68,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you both come here at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.03,0:09:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mam’zelle!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.35,0:09:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Bien. {??????? guessing}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.13,0:09:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are, twins! \NWould you take this to the classroom for me?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.40,0:09:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.21,0:09:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s up with them?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.64,0:09:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they come.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.76,0:09:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you coming in here?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.73,0:10:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I swapped beds with Vera.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.02,0:10:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! With Vera?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.94,0:10:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.21,0:10:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I also swapped with Doris.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.82,0:10:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.90,0:10:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera! You knew, didn’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.10,0:10:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.82,0:10:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Not like we plotted it together. \NRight, Doris?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.72,0:10:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly. We were each asked separately. \NRight, Vera?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.62,0:10:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.05,0:10:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, end this silly quarrel already.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.23,0:10:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You stubborn twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.17,0:10:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Twins?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.55,0:10:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That was silly. You really didn't have to say it, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.24,0:10:59.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,If only Janet wasn't teasing us still, \Nwe might've made up by now.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.89,0:11:03.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,I’ve never quarrelled this long with Isabel before.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.03,0:11:05.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,And the cause was nothing much.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.43,0:11:07.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,So why am I being so obstinate?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.23,0:11:11.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Isabel is usually the first to try to make up...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.42,0:11:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat must be waiting for me to give in.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.54,0:11:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’d be easy enough...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.61,0:11:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But why must it always be me?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.46,0:11:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our long-awaited birthday...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.13,0:11:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Will be utterly spoiled at this rate.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.47,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.94,0:11:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat and I are going into town to do the shopping. \NWanna come with us?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.26,0:11:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.52,0:11:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pass today. {??? nc what's that yosu/yusu}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.87,0:12:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.28,0:12:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, then. \NLet's go, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.81,0:12:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. That will do nicely.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.58,0:12:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Miss Roberts, \Nhave you taken notice of the O'Sullivan situation?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.11,0:12:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I most certainly did.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.12,0:12:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems they had \Na most uncharacteristic quarrel.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.72,0:12:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They have not spoken for three days, it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.84,0:12:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My word! Three whole days?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.56,0:12:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause must be trifling, but it seems they're locked in a battle of stubbornness.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.39,0:12:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One can well believe it of those two.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.63,0:12:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They are displeased at being treated \Nas one in all things.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.07,0:12:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A sure sign they are growing up, perhaps.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.57,0:12:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed; they are dependable girls, \Nand I trust they will settle it between themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.38,0:12:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall watch and see for the present.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.08,0:13:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Perhaps they need \Nsome little push to make up?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.40,0:13:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness, I do wish they’d stop this nonsense.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.37,0:13:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Really! At this rate, we'll never see the feast \Nthey might've prepared for their birthday. {basically very thinly veiled saying "we won't be able to pig out on their feast"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.16,0:13:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Never fear, Joan. When a good feast \Nfinally appears before you,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.46,0:13:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll forget all your worries and just dig in. {???? kinda contradicts the previous sentence and im pretty confident in that?}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.14,0:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, Doris!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.80,0:13:20.12,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Ah! Sorry, my bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.12,0:13:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We have tried many ways to make them reconcile, \Nbut every time it only made matters worse. {/deepened the grudge}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.51,0:13:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything we can do?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.11,0:13:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing clear is that both are \Nfrightfully obstinate, and aren't going to budge.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.54,0:13:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.98,0:13:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They are usually so approachable and pleasant.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.95,0:13:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They merely seem tangled \Nin their feelings this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.29,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, they must not be allowed \Nseparate parties.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.42,0:13:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That's exactly it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.42,0:13:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.56,0:13:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't allow them \Nto hold separate parties.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.83,0:13:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.63,0:13:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We will all insist that we will only attend \Nif the two celebrate together.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.47,0:13:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! That's a capital notion, all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.44,0:13:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If they celebrate together, \Nthey may well make up naturally.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.21,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed. But that is our last resort.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.24,0:14:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If by Saturday they are still at odds, \Nwe shall all declare it so.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.61,0:14:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pair of tiresome twins they are.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.74,0:14:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us leave it there for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.79,0:14:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Patricia, Isabel...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.13,0:14:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.59,0:14:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress wishes to see you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.97,0:14:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the headmistress’s room after school. Understood?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.14,0:14:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, miss.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.12,0:14:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, and also, change into \Nyour work smocks before going. {作業着 = work clothes; fatigues}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.64,0:14:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness me, quarrelling over birthday parties?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.28,0:14:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some responsibility in this matter then. {meaning "I can't just sit back and watch, this is my area of resp. too"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.88,0:14:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you shouldn't bother... {lit: to say responsibilty... - could mean just about anything}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.72,0:14:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What you said during \Nthe weekly address was right. {??? lit: you only taught us the right thing - assuming it's about the speech at the beginning of the ep, about lavish parties}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.49,0:14:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Headmistress, didn't you mean to tell us
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.13,0:14:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's wrong to think \Nthe answer lies in lavish spending? {?? lit:in other words, it's all right if you spend money, that kind of thinking is no good, isn't that right?}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.86,0:14:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That is part of it too.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.30,0:15:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What really worries me is that birthdays seem to have turned into nothing more
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.40,0:15:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,than excuses for overindulgence and rowdiness.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.12,0:15:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But when one marks the day of her birth, \Nsurely it's meant to be enjoyed in cheerful company? {lit: if everyone spends it marrily, isn't that good}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.14,0:15:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? The day of your birth?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.35,0:15:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all a birthday is to you?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.53,0:15:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you two, work together \Nand plant these rose saplings.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.26,0:15:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.96,0:15:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care not to spike yourselves. {probably "yourself" and not the rose}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.64,0:15:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My German friend sent me these roses.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.92,0:15:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a new variety.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.34,0:15:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It will bear great, pure white blooms.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.21,0:15:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents are fond of roses too, \Nand we often helped tend them.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.75,0:15:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that is most comforting.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.45,0:15:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Mum used to say, when tending flowers, \Nspeak to them kindly.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.46,0:16:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Praise and encourage them gently, \Nand they will grow fair.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.83,0:16:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, that is so.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.00,0:16:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like talking to the child \Nin the mother’s womb:
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.90,0:16:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with gentleness and affection.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.97,0:16:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And did the roses bloom finely?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.20,0:16:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, of course they did!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.89,0:16:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And how did you feel when you saw them?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.74,0:16:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so delighted \NI wanted to cuddle them like babies! {oozuri = rubbing cheeks together (as a display of affection); pressing cheeks together}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.85,0:16:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I even boasted of them to the postman!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.60,0:16:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother, too, must surely \Nhave spoken tenderly to you
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.96,0:16:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,each day while you were still inside her.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.38,0:16:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you suppose \Nshe felt when you were born?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.90,0:16:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What joy, what pride, \Nwhat a radiant moment it must have been.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.41,0:16:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The day your parents, with hearts brimming over with love,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.85,0:16:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,brought you into the world—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.05,0:16:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what your birthday is.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.62,0:17:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For your mother, it's the {anniversary of the }day \Nshe bore you and became a mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.32,0:17:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For your father, the day he became a father.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.26,0:17:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A day of remembrance for Dad and Mum? {/anniversary}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.08,0:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought of it like that before.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.18,0:17:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense. It is a remembrance \Ntucked deep in your parents’ hearts,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.34,0:17:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and since no one marks it outwardly, \Nyou scarcely notice it.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.13,0:17:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But we live our lives upheld by many—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.21,0:17:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,family, friends, neighbours, teachers,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.60,0:17:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,our seniors—and it is a splendid thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.92,0:17:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Think on that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.79,0:17:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that is enough gardening for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.56,0:17:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall have lovely blossoms in time, you’ll see.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.01,0:17:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us look forward to them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.37,0:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.20,0:17:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that reminds me.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.07,0:17:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a parcel from home for you at the Matron’s. \NRun along and fetch it.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.58,0:18:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, will do!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.81,0:18:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse us!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.24,0:18:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Blimey!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.96,0:18:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Mum wanted us to invite \Nthe whole school to a feast.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.73,0:18:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a present for us!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.10,0:18:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.69,0:18:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How sweet! \NMother made them herself!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.00,0:18:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a card!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.92,0:18:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"I long to see your faces, grown a little more, Patricia and Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.33,0:18:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A very happy birthday to you both."
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.14,0:19:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought birthdays \Nwere simply for getting festive. {/being made a fuss of/celebrating}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.08,0:19:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So did I. But really, we have \Nour mother, father, and everyone else
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.61,0:19:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to thank that we are here at all \Nto celebrate our birthday!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.40,0:19:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A birthday is a day for gratitude.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.66,0:19:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what Headmistress meant!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.52,0:19:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.68,0:19:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, let’s celebrate as well...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.50,0:19:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum's remembrance day! {okasan-tachi = dad and mom, but idk how to write it in here and make it reasonable cps}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.80,0:19:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll write a card...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.03,0:19:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And post it express! {so it arrives in time - dunno how to word it here}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.53,0:19:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And enough of this quarrel.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.59,0:19:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sick and tired \Nof not speaking to you for days.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.17,0:19:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been far too long.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.98,0:19:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s miserable not having you to talk to.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.98,0:19:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.06,0:19:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m sorry too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.05,0:19:50.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mother, happy day of giving birth. {/day of becomign a mom}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.36,0:19:53.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Father, happy day of becoming a father. {/your fathership remembrance day}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.00,0:19:57.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,With all our thanks on our birthday—Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.11,0:19:58.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,and Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.57,0:20:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Day of giving birth and day of becoming a father, eh? Interesting.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.79,0:20:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our little girls... \NWho knew they even think of things like that? {probably means "they even consider how we feel"}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.31,0:20:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}because{\i0} they're our little girls. {?? hope he means this - it could only be these chibi-san, and not someone else}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.84,0:20:11.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,P.S.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.66,0:20:17.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the presents and all the delicious sweets and tinned things.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.25,0:20:19.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's looking to be a splendid party.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.25,0:20:21.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,We’ll write again with all the details.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.29,0:20:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This chocolate cake is heavenly, Pat, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.08,0:20:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And that pie too! \NDid your mother make everything?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.37,0:20:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She did. Why, when Mum’s in the kitchen, \Nshe’s a regular magician.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.10,0:20:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wish you could taste \Nher orange soufflé!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.44,0:20:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.16,0:20:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s hope you two have inherited \Nsome of her gift, our dear twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.21,0:20:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.05,0:20:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But truly, I am glad you two made up.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.78,0:20:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought today’s party \Nwould be ruined altogether.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.95,0:20:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, quite so. \NYou gave us quite the scare.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.54,0:21:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all on edge. \NJoan most of all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.16,0:21:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.25,0:21:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, you two are a trial!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.20,0:21:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sorry. We were glad to at last realise \Nhow much you’d all been worried about us.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.57,0:21:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s thanks to everyone that we’ve been able \Nto have this party today.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.24,0:21:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re ever so grateful!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.19,0:21:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s best when you two stay the jolly twins we know.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.54,0:21:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We think so too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.91,0:21:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let’s open that tin as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.68,0:21:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.12,0:21:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Binks!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.62,0:21:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do something, Kathleen! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.99,0:21:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Binks! Leave it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.16,0:21:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter with Binks?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.66,0:21:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.06,0:21:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis, won’t you have a slice \Nof this delicious homemade cake with us?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.60,0:21:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the twins’ birthday party today!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.02,0:21:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My! Many happy returns, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.97,0:21:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Did you say a birthday party?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.72,0:21:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome to join us too, Mam'zelle!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.91,0:21:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Merci! Be there at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.02,0:23:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet’s gone quite dotty \Nover fortune-telling with Tarot cards.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.75,0:23:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all because Margo in the fifth form does readings that are said to be uncannily accurate.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.49,0:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says they don’t believe in such things—\Nbut all the same, they’re curious!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.08,0:23:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortune-telling! Everyone’s losing their heads over it. It’s ridiculous!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.26,0:23:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And now Janet says that three disasters \Nare going to befall Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.92,0:23:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As if! It’s obvious nonsense!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.24,0:23:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.74,0:24:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Great Tarot Fortune-Telling Craze!" {タロット占い大流行!}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.36,0:24:04.79,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 18 \NThe Great Tarot Fortune-Telling Craze! {タロット占い大流行!}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.37,0:24:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss it!
